    requiredFields: ['timestamp', 'hostname', 'network_interface', 'network_state', 'message', 'process', 'kernel_timestamp'],
    detectionLogic: 'Alert when kernel messages indicate a network interface has entered promiscuous mode (PROMISC flag set). Correlate with the process responsible and determine if legitimate monitoring tools (tcpdump, wireshark, zeek) or unauthorized sniffing.',
    falsePositives: ['Legitimate network monitoring tools (tcpdump, Zeek/Bro, Suricata) used by network team', 'Container networking (Docker bridge, Kubernetes CNI) enabling promiscuous mode', 'Network troubleshooting sessions by authorized administrators'],
    tuningGuidance: 'Maintain an allowlist of hosts authorized to run packet capture (IDS sensors, network taps). Alert immediately on any non-authorized host entering promiscuous mode. Track duration — brief promiscuous mode during container startup is normal.',
    investigationWorkflow: '1. Identify which host and interface entered promiscuous mode\n2. Determine the process that triggered the mode change\n3. Check if the host is an authorized monitoring/IDS sensor\n4. Review if this coincides with a known troubleshooting ticket\n5. Look for data exfiltration indicators (large outbound transfers from the host)\n6. If unauthorized, immediately isolate the host and preserve forensic evidence',
