    detectionLogic: 'Alert when kernel or mount logs show a filesystem being remounted with read-write permissions, particularly for /, /boot, /usr, or other normally read-only mounts. Flag any remount on immutable infrastructure hosts.',
    falsePositives: ['Legitimate system updates requiring temporary read-write access to /boot', 'Package manager operations on systems using read-only root', 'Embedded systems or containers during initialization'],
    tuningGuidance: 'Identify which hosts use read-only root filesystems (immutable infrastructure). Any remount on those hosts is critical. For standard hosts, focus on /boot and /usr remounts outside of package management windows.',
    investigationWorkflow: '1. Identify which filesystem was remounted and on which host\n2. Determine if this correlates with a package update or maintenance window\n3. Check what process initiated the remount operation\n4. Look for file modifications to system binaries after the remount\n5. Verify filesystem was returned to read-only after legitimate operations\n6. On immutable infrastructure, treat any remount as a critical incident requiring immediate investigation',
