    detectionLogic: 'Alert when cron executes commands containing suspicious patterns: reverse shells (bash -i, /dev/tcp), download utilities (curl|wget piped to sh/bash), encoded commands (base64 -d), or commands running from /tmp, /dev/shm, or other world-writable locations. Also alert on new cron entries for root.',
    falsePositives: ['Legitimate automation scripts using curl/wget for health checks', 'System update scripts that download and execute', 'Monitoring agents running periodic checks via cron'],
    tuningGuidance: 'Build a baseline of known cron jobs per host from initial deployment. Alert on any new cron entry not in the baseline. Focus high-severity alerts on commands with shell redirection to network sockets or execution from temporary directories.',
    investigationWorkflow: '1. Identify the cron command, the user executing it, and the host\n2. Check if this cron job exists in the approved baseline for the host\n3. Examine the command for obfuscation (base64, hex encoding, variable expansion)\n4. If the command downloads content, determine the source URL reputation\n5. Check /var/spool/cron and /etc/cron.d for recently modified files\n6. Look for the cron job creation event — who or what added it and when',
