      detectionLogic: 'Pattern match request_uri and query_string for SQL injection indicators: UNION SELECT, OR 1=1, single quote followed by SQL keywords, comment sequences (--), WAITFOR DELAY, BENCHMARK(), information_schema references, and hex-encoded SQL. Alert on both successful (2xx) and blocked (4xx/5xx) attempts as blocked attempts indicate active targeting.',
      falsePositives: ['Security scanning tools running authorized vulnerability assessments', 'Web application firewalls generating test traffic', 'Legitimate application queries containing SQL-like keywords in content fields'],
      tuningGuidance: 'Exclude authorized scanner source IPs. Tune URI patterns to exclude known application paths that legitimately contain SQL-like strings. Focus highest severity on successful (200) responses to injection attempts. Correlate with WAF logs for blocked attempts.',
      investigationWorkflow: '1. Examine the full request URI and query string for injection payload\n2. Determine if the response was successful (200) or blocked (403/500)\n3. Check source IP reputation and geolocation\n4. Review all requests from the same source IP for attack progression\n5. Assess which application/endpoint was targeted\n6. If successful response returned, investigate for data exfiltration',
