      tuningGuidance: 'Focus on POST requests to login endpoints. Look for patterns across multiple source IPs (distributed attack). Set alert when unique source IPs to login endpoint exceeds baseline. Track success rate per source IP block. Consider CAPTCHA or rate limiting integration.',
      investigationWorkflow: '1. Identify the targeted login endpoint and timeframe\n2. Count unique source IPs and estimate attack scale\n3. Calculate overall success rate — any successful logins?\n4. Review user agent patterns — are they rotating or consistent?\n5. Check for successful logins that should be immediately investigated\n6. Implement rate limiting and CAPTCHA if not already in place',
