      detectionLogic: 'Alert on EventID 4624 where LogonType is 9 (NewCredentials) and AuthenticationPackage is NTLM. Filter out domain controllers as source. Correlate with the source_network_address to identify the originating host. Escalate when the target account is a privileged or service account.',
      falsePositives: ['Legitimate use of runas /netonly for administrative tasks', 'Scheduled tasks running under alternate credentials', 'Some backup software that uses NewCredentials logon type'],
      tuningGuidance: 'Exclude known domain controllers from source addresses. Build a baseline of accounts that legitimately use LogonType 9. Correlate with asset inventory to validate source hosts. Set higher severity for privileged account targets.',
      investigationWorkflow: '1. Identify the source_network_address — is this a known administrative workstation?\n2. Determine the target_username — is this a privileged or service account?\n3. Check if there is a corresponding 4625 (failed logon) preceding the success\n4. Look for lateral movement following this logon (additional 4624 from the target machine)\n5. Verify with the account owner whether runas /netonly was used legitimately\n6. Check for Mimikatz/secretsdump artifacts on the source host',
