      investigationWorkflow: '1. IMMEDIATE: Isolate the affected host — LSASS crash is high-confidence credential dump\n2. Check faulting_module — what DLL or component caused the crash?\n3. Look for preceding Sysmon Event 10 with TargetImage=lsass.exe\n4. Search for process creation events for known dump tools (procdump, mimikatz, comsvcs.dll)\n5. Check for crash dump files that may contain credentials\n6. Assume credentials on this host are compromised — begin password reset procedures',
