      tuningGuidance: 'Build an allowlist of known legitimate modules in non-standard paths. Focus on modules loaded into Windows system processes. Correlate with file creation events to determine when the suspicious DLL was dropped. Higher severity for modules in temp directories or with random-looking names.',
      investigationWorkflow: '1. Identify the faulting_module and its full path — is it in a suspicious location?\n2. Check if the module file is signed and by a trusted publisher\n3. Determine the faulting_application — is this a critical system process?\n4. Look for file creation events showing when the module was placed on disk\n5. Check the module hash against threat intelligence\n6. Correlate with Sysmon Event 7 (ImageLoaded) for additional context',
