      detectionLogic: 'Correlate EventID 1000 (Application Error) with EventID 4624 (successful logon) on the same host within a 60-second window. Focus on crashes of unusual or non-standard applications during logon. Escalate when the crashing application is from a temporary directory or has no valid signature. Exclude known logon-time applications (startup programs, profile scripts).',
      falsePositives: ['Legitimate startup applications crashing due to missing dependencies', 'Outdated logon scripts encountering errors', 'Profile loading issues causing application failures at logon'],
      tuningGuidance: 'Build a baseline of applications that commonly crash at logon time. Exclude known problematic but benign startup applications. Focus on crashes from applications in user-writable paths. Set higher priority when the crash involves credential-related processes.',
      investigationWorkflow: '1. Identify the crashing application and its path — is it a known logon-time program?\n2. Check the time delta between logon and crash — how closely correlated?\n3. Determine if the application exists in startup locations (Run keys, Startup folder)\n4. Check if the faulting_application is signed and legitimate\n5. Look for the application being dropped to disk before the logon event\n6. Review the crashing process for credential access patterns',
