      tags: ['security', 'lolbin', 'living-off-the-land', 'proxy-execution', 'defense-evasion', 'windows-sysmon'],
      requiredFields: ['event_id', 'timestamp', 'computer', 'image', 'command_line', 'parent_image', 'parent_command_line', 'user', 'process_id', 'hashes'],
      detectionLogic: 'Alert on Sysmon Event 1 (Process Create) where image matches known LOLBins and command_line contains suspicious patterns: certutil with -urlcache or -decode, mshta with http/javascript/vbscript, regsvr32 with /s /u /i:http or scrobj.dll, rundll32 with javascript or suspicious DLL paths. Correlate parent process for full attack chain.',
      falsePositives: ['IT administrators using certutil for legitimate certificate management', 'Enterprise software using rundll32 for DLL execution', 'Some legitimate applications that call regsvr32 during installation'],
      tuningGuidance: 'Focus on LOLBin executions with network-related arguments (URLs, http). Whitelist specific parent/child process pairs known to be legitimate. Alert on any LOLBin execution from an interactive user session. Track LOLBin usage baseline per host to detect anomalies.',
      investigationWorkflow: '1. Review the full command_line — what is the LOLBin being asked to do?\n2. Identify parent_image — what process launched the LOLBin?\n3. Check for network connections from the LOLBin process\n4. Determine if files were downloaded or created by the execution\n5. Check if the parent process chain indicates user interaction or automated execution\n6. Look for subsequent process creation or persistence mechanisms after LOLBin execution',
