      detectionLogic: 'Alert when a single target_username with administrative privileges (determined by EventID 4672 correlation or group membership) authenticates to more than 10 unique forwarding_computer hosts within a 24-hour window. WEF provides fleet-wide visibility to detect this spread. Compare against historical baseline for the account.',
      falsePositives: ['IT administrators performing fleet-wide maintenance', 'Vulnerability scanning tools using privileged credentials', 'Deployment tools authenticating to many hosts for software push'],
      tuningGuidance: 'Establish per-account baselines for normal host authentication spread. Exclude known management service accounts with expected wide reach. Set dynamic thresholds based on historical behavior. Alert when an account exceeds 2x its normal host count. Higher severity for accounts not in expected admin groups.',
      investigationWorkflow: '1. Identify target_username — is this a known administrator account?\n2. Compare current host count against the account historical baseline\n3. Check if a maintenance activity or deployment justifies wide access\n4. Review the hosts being accessed — are they in the account normal scope?\n5. Look for data access or command execution on the target hosts\n6. Verify with the account owner whether the activity is authorized',
