      detectionLogic: 'Alert on indicators of remote execution: (1) PSEXESVC.exe parent spawning child processes, (2) wmiprvse.exe spawning cmd/powershell/script interpreters, (3) wsmprovhost.exe (WinRM) launching command interpreters, (4) services.exe spawning processes with remote service creation patterns. Correlate with inbound network connections on ports 445, 135, 5985, 5986.',
      falsePositives: ['Legitimate IT administration using PsExec for remote management', 'SCCM/Configuration Manager using WMI for inventory and deployment', 'Automated patching systems using WinRM for remote execution'],
      tuningGuidance: 'Whitelist known IT admin accounts and management servers by source IP. Create exceptions for approved remote management tools. Focus on unexpected user accounts, non-standard hours, and targets outside management subnets.',
      investigationWorkflow: '1. Identify the parent process (PSEXESVC, wmiprvse, wsmprovhost) and what it spawned\n2. Determine the source device by correlating inbound network connections\n3. Check if the user account is authorized for remote administration\n4. Review what commands were executed on the target\n5. Map additional targets — did the same source IP connect to other endpoints?\n6. Check timing — does this align with known maintenance windows?',
